  "prompt": "Is it worth for a good programmer to apply for UK position if you have only 1 year experience?",
  "response": "It depends on several factors:\n\nPros:\n\u2705 UK tech market is quite open to junior developers\n\u2705 Many companies hire programmers with 1-2 years experience\n\u2705 Some companies value skills over years of experience\n\u2705 Competitive salaries compared to many other countries\n\u2705 Good career growth opportunities\n\nChallenges:\n\u2757 Visa requirements can be complex\n\u2757 Some senior roles might require more experience\n\u2757 Competitive job market, especially in tech hubs like London\n\nRecommended steps:\n1. Check your specific skills and technology stack\n2. Prepare a strong portfolio/GitHub\n3. Have good communication skills\n4. Consider these visa options:\n- Skilled Worker Visa\n- Global Talent Visa\n- Tech Nation Visa\n\nGood opportunities for 1-year experienced programmers:\n- Junior developer roles\n- Entry-level positions\n- Startups\n- Companies with training programs\n\nSalary range for 1-year experience:\n- \u00a325,000 - \u00a335,000 typically\n- London might offer higher rates\n\nAdvice:\n- Apply confidently\n- Highlight your skills\n- Be open to learning\n- Network through LinkedIn, tech events\n\nOverall: Definitely worth applying if you're skilled and motivated!",
